1
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,667
<i> The door is open.</i>

2
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,067
<i>You should be
double-checking those.</i>

3
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,833
<i> What? Noah's here?</i>

4
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:48,667
<i>- Manuel?
- Noah?</i>

5
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:49,900
<i>You have no place here anymore!</i>

6
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,600
<i> Darn you!</i>

7
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,000
<i> Go back to your wife!</i>

8
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:55,967
<i>You have no place
in this family anymore!</i>

9
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,500
<i>And you? Are you even part
of this family?</i>

10
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:59,167
<i> You, bastard!</i>

11
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,333
<i> Noah!</i>

12
00:01:00,467 --> 00:01:02,100
<i>Auntie Andrea, remember what
I said, okay?</i>

13
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,833
<i>Once grandfather says sorry,
please forgive him.</i>

14
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:06,167
<i> You betrayed us!</i>

15
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,833
<i>I don't think they deserve this!</i>

16
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,700
<i> This is a family matter.</i>

17
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,233
<i> And you're not part of this!</i>

18
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:12,633
<i> What's missing?</i>

19
00:01:12,767 --> 00:01:15,000
<i>The monthly sales report
from our five branches.</i>

20
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:17,067
<i> I can't find it.</i>

21
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,800
<i>I thought you were
getting married.</i>

22
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:20,333
<i> I can't love anymore.</i>

23
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:24,367
<i>There's only one man I see
walking with me down the aisle.</i>

24
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,167
<i> It's you.</i>

25
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:27,367
<i> I couldn't do it.</i>

26
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:28,533
<i> I failed you.</i>

27
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,533
<i> I forgive you.</i>

28
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:31,567
<i> Alice!</i>

29
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,167
<i> What's the plan?</i>

30
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:44,567
Miss Felma.

31
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:48,800
What is it, Jessica?

32
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:56,500
I just wanted to say
thank you for everything.

33
00:01:56,633 --> 00:02:01,500
We're very sorry for all
the trouble we've caused.

34
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:02,900
Don't worry about that.

35
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,567
Dad was right.

36
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:08,267
You're so kind.

37
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:13,400
Despite all that happened
in the past,

38
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:17,000
you allowed us to stay here.

39
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:20,200
I'm the product of the sin
that mom and dad committed

40
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:22,133
against you.

41
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:27,267
And yet, you were so kind to me.

42
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:32,867
You never showed me
that you were angry.

43
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,767
Hush now.

44
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:47,467
I was never angry at you,
not even once.

45
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:54,867
You had nothing to do

46
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,733
with whatever your mom and dad
did to me.

47
00:02:57,867 --> 00:03:01,800
How could I ever
be angry at you?

48
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:04,400
You're such a kind child.

49
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:06,700
So loving.

50
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:11,900
You never left your dad's side.

51
00:03:12,033 --> 00:03:13,200
You stayed with him...

52
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:20,167
stood by him,
and fought for him.

53
00:03:23,867 --> 00:03:25,867
Thank you, Miss Felma.

54
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:33,200
Stop calling me Miss Felma.

55
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,833
Just Aunt Felma.

56
00:03:35,967 --> 00:03:38,700
Thank you so much...

57
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,367
Aunt Felma.

58
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,533
Come here.

59
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:54,067
I'm so happy for you, Dad.

60
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:59,100
I hope Andrea and Jeffrey
can forgive you someday.

61
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,667
Oh, sweetheart.

62
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:03,267
I'm not expecting that anymore.

63
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:06,267
Your siblings
are just too angry at me.

64
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,433
Don't lose hope.

65
00:04:08,567 --> 00:04:12,200
Andrea and Jeffrey
are good people.

66
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,667
I witnessed it.

67
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,800
It feels good to be part
of their family.

68
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:21,867
Even though I was with them
just once,

69
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,233
I could feel that
they were happy.

70
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:26,333
I wish I had a family like that.

71
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:31,600
I wish mom had been as kind
as Miss Felma was.

72
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,800
Don't worry, Dear.

73
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:37,900
Even if it's just
the two of us,

74
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:41,233
I'll make sure we're happy.

75
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:43,700
I know you'll do that.

76
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:49,000
But, Dad, mom will never
stop looking for us.

77
00:04:49,133 --> 00:04:52,100
No, Dear.
Actually, I have a plan.

78
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:55,267
We won't stay long at the
apartment we're moving into.

79
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,033
We'll go to the province

80
00:04:57,167 --> 00:04:59,567
so your mom can't find us
anymore.

81
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:02,500
We'll be away from Coleen.

82
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:05,433
We'll just come back here later.

83
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:07,333
Once your mom gets tired
of looking,

84
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:09,500
she'll go back to Canada.

85
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,600
That sounds like
a good plan, Dad.

86
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,267
Miss Martinez?

87
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:31,633
Miss Antonio?

88
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:33,367
Nice to meet you.

89
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,067
You look familiar.

90
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,067
I think I know you.

91
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,833
Sorry, have we met before?

92
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:43,033
I can't remember anymore.

93
00:05:43,167 --> 00:05:45,367
I get that a lot.

94
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,700
Many people say
I look like someone.

95
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,933
Sometimes it's a celebrity,

96
00:05:51,067 --> 00:05:56,300
sometimes just someone
they know.

97
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:58,733
I think I have a generic face.

98
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:00,200
Oh, yeah!

99
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:02,767
You really do look
like a celebrity!

100
00:06:04,167 --> 00:06:08,467
Anyway, are you sure you
want to be an FMP dealer?

101
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:10,167
Yes, very much.

102
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,767
Very good.

103
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:15,800
I'm going to discuss to you
the FMP distributorship package.

104
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,233
Come. Oh, wait.

105
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:20,500
I'll introduce you to one
of the owners of FMP.

106
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:22,367
Sir Noah, this is Miss Martinez,

107
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,900
a future business partner
of FMP.

108
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,267
Hi, Sir.

109
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,833
And soon to be ex-co-owner.

110
00:06:27,967 --> 00:06:28,600
Ex?

111
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:29,667
Ex...

112
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,267
Where is he going?

113
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,333
Ma'am, have a seat first.

114
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:34,567
Come here. Come this way.

115
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:38,100
You can have coffee
as much as you like.

116
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,000
Wait for me.

117
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:40,300
I'll come back. Promise.

118
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,300
Coffee?

119
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,000
Yeah. Thank you.

120
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,067
Ma'am Andrea.

121
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,500
Didn't I tell you not
to bother me right now?

122
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:59,200
Where is it?

123
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:02,067
Your staff did tell me...

124
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,400
but I insisted.

125
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,900
I'm Joel Santiago.

126
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:18,167
I picked up these files of yours

127
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:20,467
when you bumped into my friend
the other day.

128
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,933
- Remember?
- Yeah!

129
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,267
I've been looking for this.

130
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,633
I thought I wouldn't
find this anymore.

131
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:27,333
Thank you.

132
00:07:27,467 --> 00:07:28,200
Have a seat.

133
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,467
Just a thank you?

134
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,367
Is there no reward?

135
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:40,367
Of course!

136
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:43,067
We have plenty
of products here at FMP.

137
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:47,267
We have<i> sisig</i> ,<i> tapa</i> ,
longanisa, tocino...

138
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,067
What would you like?

139
00:07:48,233 --> 00:07:49,700
- How many?
- You're cute.

140
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,300
I was just joking.

141
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,900
Coffee would be enough.

142
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,600
Coffee? Sure!

143
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:59,467
- Noah! Noah, what's this?
- Paz, please.

144
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,133
Noah, you haven't
signed this contract.

145
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:11,600
Why are you packing
your things?

146
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,500
I'm leaving.

147
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:19,333
Leaving, as in resigning?

148
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:20,433
Yes.

149
00:08:22,867 --> 00:08:23,833
But my share remains.

150
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:26,633
I'm still a member
of the board.

151
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:31,500
But don't worry, Felma.

152
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:34,100
I'll just send a representative
for our board meetings.

153
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,433
Okay.

154
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:40,933
That's it?

155
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:45,800
Felma, it feels like you
can just let me go so easily.

156
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:48,167
What do you want me to do?

157
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,233
Should I stop you?

158
00:08:49,367 --> 00:08:50,767
Yes.

159
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,933
Felma, even if
it's just pretend.

160
00:08:53,067 --> 00:08:54,633
So that at least in the end,

161
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,000
I can feel that
I mattered to you,

162
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:58,533
that you didn't want
to let me go.

163
00:08:58,667 --> 00:09:00,667
You're important to me.

164
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,800
More than you know.

165
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,033
I wouldn't be here,
or there wouldn't even be an FMP

166
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:08,533
if you hadn't trusted me
to grow it.

167
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:09,367
My god, wait a minute.

168
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,800
What's going on between you two?

169
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:13,467
Can't you just settle this
with some talking?

170
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,967
Sorry, but don't think I want
you to leave because I don't.

171
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,833
I don't.

172
00:09:19,967 --> 00:09:22,400
I owe you so much, but...

173
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:25,067
it looks like we just
can't get along anymore.

174
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:28,767
Noah!

175
00:09:39,967 --> 00:09:41,933
Noah! Noah! Wait!

176
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:43,600
Noah, wait!

177
00:09:46,533 --> 00:09:48,800
We have a lot of coffee here
in the pantry.

178
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:49,900
Want some?

179
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:51,800
Pantry?

180
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:54,667
I thought we were
going to a coffee shop.

181
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,533
Coffee shop?

182
00:09:57,667 --> 00:10:01,633
You never said you wanted coffee
from a coffee shop.

183
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,733
Okay.

184
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:07,767
Okay?

185
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,367
<i> Noah! Noah!</i>

186
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,833
<i> Noah! Don't be so rash, okay?</i>

187
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,833
Excuse me.

188
00:10:20,967 --> 00:10:22,167
Paz, please.

189
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,600
Don't follow me anymore.

190
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:26,633
My decision won't change.

191
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:29,100
- But, Noah...
- Uncle, what's happening?

192
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:31,833
Your mom and Noah
are fighting again.

193
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:33,800
He says he's leaving
the company.

194
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,267
What?

195
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:36,700
Uncle, please don't.

196
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,933
Can we still talk this out?

197
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:41,467
I'm tired, Andrea.

198
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,867
I feel like I've been played
too many times.

199
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:48,367
What are you and mom fighting
about this time?

200
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:49,533
It's about your dad.

201
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:54,300
I found out something
about him and your mom.

202
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:56,200
What?

203
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:58,067
Just ask your mom.

204
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,833
Uncle...

205
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,033
Andeng.

206
00:11:15,267 --> 00:11:16,067
Mom, what's happening?

207
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,800
Why is Uncle Noah leaving?

208
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:20,267
What did he say?

209
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:23,200
He said he found out
something about your ex.

210
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:24,367
What is it?

211
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:25,600
What did he tell you?

212
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:28,133
Mom, if I already knew,
I wouldn't even be asking you.

213
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:33,933
Sorry.

214
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:34,967
Just go to the pantry.

215
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:36,033
Have a coffee.

216
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:37,400
No, I'm okay.

217
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:38,700
Thank you.

218
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:42,733
Back to work!

219
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:51,267
Madame, I'm sorry.

220
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,633
There was just a little hiccup.

221
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:55,200
No problem.

222
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,900
But I'm just curious.

223
00:11:58,033 --> 00:11:59,933
What's the issue
with the owners?

224
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:07,767
We talked the other day.

225
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,433
Our breakup came up again.

226
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:15,300
Then he got mad at me
because I said I'm done.

227
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:16,433
Mom, that's not what he said.

228
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:19,000
He said he found out something.
What is it?

229
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:20,533
That's all there is to it, Dear.

230
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:22,300
Mom, tell me the truth.

231
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:23,733
- Please.
- Andrea!

232
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:26,500
Jeffrey and I have noticed
many things

233
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:28,167
about you and Coleen.

234
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:30,833
You two are hiding
something from us.

235
00:12:30,967 --> 00:12:32,700
And now Uncle Noah's leaving

236
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:35,567
because you, guys,
have been playing him.

237
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:36,767
Mom, come on.

238
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,567
Please just tell us the truth.

239
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:41,100
Enough with the secrets, please!

240
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,233
- I don't know.
- You know,

241
00:12:50,367 --> 00:12:52,367
as a potential business partner,

242
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:55,033
I think I have the right
to know.

243
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:57,233
I'm sorry. I really don't know.

244
00:12:58,367 --> 00:12:59,600
I'll just call you.

245
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,333
Sorry.

246
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,267
Okay.

247
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,800
You're right.

248
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:14,700
I'm hiding Manuel.

249
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:23,867
And that's what Noah found out.

250
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:25,967
What?

251
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:46,867
So, I think, Noah, the co-owner,
is Felma's boyfriend.

252
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,000
And they fought
over your husband.

253
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:54,333
Apparently, he found out
something about the two of them.

254
00:13:56,067 --> 00:13:59,167
He probably found out
what I found out.

255
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:01,633
That Felma's hiding my husband
and daughter.

256
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,733
I told you.

257
00:14:04,867 --> 00:14:07,667
Felma still has feelings
for my husband.

258
00:14:09,267 --> 00:14:11,300
Oh, damn yeah.

259
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,800
Speaking of the devil.

260
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:33,300
That's Noah, the co-owner.

261
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:36,967
<i> Mom!</i>

262
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:39,533
<i> Felma, stop!</i>

263
00:14:39,667 --> 00:14:41,500
<i>Who are you? Why are you hurting
my mother?</i>

264
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:48,433
That's also Felma's fiancé.

265
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,867
Wait.

266
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,767
Why?

267
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:07,967
What will you do?

268
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,200
Just wait here.

269
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:10,533
Hazel!

270
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:23,733
I'm just helping Coleen
keep Manuel and Jessica away

271
00:15:23,867 --> 00:15:28,133
because Hazel has been hurting
them.

272
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:30,600
That's all, Dear.

273
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:34,567
Once they have settled,
I won't get involved anymore.

274
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,933
Why did you do this to us?

275
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:41,333
Where are you hiding them?

276
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:43,767
Jessica's about to leave.

277
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:46,367
Mom, where are you hiding them?

278
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:47,300
I need to go.

279
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:48,267
Mom.

280
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,500
Mom, tell me where
you're hiding them.

281
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:51,267
Tell me...

282
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,233
Mom, talk to me!

283
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,333
Andeng, that's enough.

284
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:55,500
You're just going
to fight even more.

285
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:56,300
That's enough.

286
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:58,733
Enough, Child. Enough.

287
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:02,233
I don't get it, Auntie?

288
00:16:02,367 --> 00:16:05,400
Why is mom like that?

289
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:08,767
Why is she helping the guy
who cheated on her?

290
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:11,033
Doesn't she ever learn?

291
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:13,733
So what happens next?

292
00:16:13,867 --> 00:16:16,667
He's going to come back,

293
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:19,700
she'll fall for him again,
and be foolish all over again?

294
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:21,833
And she's going
to get hurt again?

295
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:26,300
Auntie, I don't want
that to happen to mom.

296
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,467
I don't want her to get hurt.

297
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,067
I don't.

298
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,567
I don't want that to happen.

299
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:38,200
That's enough.

300
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:40,367
I don't want that.

301
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:43,767
No.

302
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:55,600
What?

303
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:57,367
Hi.

304
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:00,200
You may not remember me,
but we met before.

305
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,833
I'm Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

306
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:06,367
Manuel's husband.

307
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,733
What do you want from me?

308
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:20,467
I want to know
where my husband is.

309
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:27,500
Mom won't tell me, Jeff.

310
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:28,567
Come with me to Coleen.

311
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:29,767
I need to talk to her.

312
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,433
You think she's going to tell us
where her dad's hiding?

313
00:17:32,567 --> 00:17:35,400
If she doesn't, she's really
going to lose her sister.

314
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:36,533
I'm serious!

315
00:17:36,667 --> 00:17:37,867
Then what?

316
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,433
You're going to go
after that guy?

317
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:40,600
<i> Yes!</i>

318
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:43,200
And I'll send him right back
to that Hazel.

319
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:44,433
<i> See, Jeffrey?</i>

320
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:46,833
<i>He's still messing up
our lives even now.</i>

321
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:49,067
Andrea, can you calm down?

322
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:50,067
All right, I'll come with you.

323
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,800
But wait for me.
I'm still in Tarlac.

324
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:53,567
There are lots of deliveries.

325
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,933
I can't wait for you, Jeff.

326
00:17:56,067 --> 00:17:57,333
Fine, forget it.

327
00:17:57,467 --> 00:17:58,800
I'll just book a ride
on the Sakay app.

328
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:00,367
Andrea, no! Can you please
wait...

329
00:18:16,867 --> 00:18:18,667
Are you okay?

330
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:21,167
I didn't know you
were still here.

331
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,200
Sorry, I wasn't able
to come back.

332
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:24,733
You saw what happened.

333
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:25,467
It's okay.

334
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,567
You seemed to be in a hurry.

335
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:28,500
I can give you a ride,
if you need it.

336
00:18:28,633 --> 00:18:30,033
No, it's fine. Thank you.

337
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:35,033
All right, but I'll catch up
with you one of these days.

338
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:37,500
I'll still make you pay
for that coffee.

339
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:38,767
Okay.

340
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,000
Joel!

341
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,533
Which way are you going?

342
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:50,100
And what made you think I know
where your bastard husband is?

343
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,233
When Manuel ran away from me,

344
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:54,600
I knew he'd go
straight to Felma.

345
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:55,700
And?

346
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:58,600
I heard there was chaos.

347
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,633
You and Felma had a fight.

348
00:19:00,767 --> 00:19:02,400
And I'm assuming

349
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:06,133
it's because you found out
she's hiding Manuel.

350
00:19:06,267 --> 00:19:08,567
Tell me where Manuel is.

351
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,133
I promise you...

352
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:14,333
he'll never get
near Felma again.

353
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:15,800
Noah, please.

354
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:18,000
Please tell me.

355
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:19,867
Go ahead.

356
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,733
Are you really okay with Manuel
taking Felma away from you?

357
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:44,167
So your mom kept our old photos.

358
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,433
Actually, Dad...

359
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:49,600
she threw them away.

360
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:51,300
I just secretly picked them up
after.

361
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,167
Coleen, you two look so cute!

362
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:57,600
You were just a baby
in those photos with dad.

363
00:19:57,733 --> 00:19:59,500
Yeah, I know, right?

364
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:00,767
Oh, wait.

365
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:03,567
You still don't have a new photo
together since the reunion!

366
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:05,133
Oh, yes.

367
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:06,867
Dear, can you please
take a picture of us?

368
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,400
Sure.

369
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:10,167
Give me your phone, Coleen.

370
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:12,700
It's not with me.
I left it in the room.

371
00:20:12,833 --> 00:20:13,933
Can we use your phone instead?

372
00:20:14,067 --> 00:20:15,167
- Okay!
- Send it to me, okay?

373
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,433
Okay.

374
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:17,433
Here.

375
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:23,300
Dad.

376
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:24,067
What?

377
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,767
Come on, give me a smile first.

378
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:28,533
-Smile.
-We've got a lot of poses to do.

379
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:30,367
1, 2, 3.

380
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:34,700
Now, let's do this.

381
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,500
What's that?
Why are you doing that?

382
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:37,633
Peace!

383
00:20:37,767 --> 00:20:39,867
1, 2, 3.

384
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,633
Let's do a duck face, Dad.

385
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:42,600
This is how you do that.
The pout.

386
00:20:42,733 --> 00:20:44,200
What exactly are you
making me do, Dear?

387
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:46,767
- Dad, pout now!
- We said just a photo!

388
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,500
What?

389
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:52,067
1, 2, 3!

390
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,367
Cute!

391
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,133
What are you making me do now?

392
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:56,733
- No, Dad!
- All right, that's enough.

393
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:58,100
Dad, make a pose.

394
00:20:58,233 --> 00:20:59,133
What is it this time?

395
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:00,433
Let's do this one, Dad.

396
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:02,367
Let's do this first.
Heart on the cheek!

397
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,400
Okay. Heart, heart.

398
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:08,500
1, 2, 3.

399
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:10,100
Then let's make a heart, Dad.

400
00:21:10,233 --> 00:21:11,833
Like this. That pose is already
outdated.

401
00:21:11,967 --> 00:21:12,600
You should do it
like this instead.

402
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:13,733
What's that?

403
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:16,500
Straighten this finger.

404
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:19,300
- 1, 2, 3, smile, Dad!
- Oh, youth these days.

405
00:21:22,067 --> 00:21:22,833
Okay, one last.

406
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:23,867
Then let's take a groupie.

407
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,033
Oh, let's take a groupie now.

408
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:27,500
- That'll be the last.
- Okay.

409
00:21:27,633 --> 00:21:29,733
- Come here, come here.
- I'll think of other poses.

410
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:32,033
1, 2, 3.

411
00:21:32,167 --> 00:21:33,000
Smile!

412
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:36,833
Sir.

413
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,267
- Uncle.
- Uncle.

414
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,833
- Please give me your blessing.
- Hello.

415
00:21:39,967 --> 00:21:41,067
- Please give me your blessing.
- How are you?

416
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,033
What made you come here?

417
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:42,700
Yes, Bro.

418
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:44,167
Felma's not here, right?

419
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:44,967
And?

420
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:47,700
I saw a new apartment.

421
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:50,033
It's also cheap
and closer to here, too.

422
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:51,500
That's actually
why I dropped by.

423
00:21:51,633 --> 00:21:54,033
I thought you might
be interested.

424
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:56,967
I'm here to collect your deposit
and advance payment.

425
00:21:57,100 --> 00:22:00,567
Bro, you can move in
as early as tomorrow.

426
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:02,467
All right, sounds good.
We'll take it.

427
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,200
Jessica, get our money.

428
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:05,833
Yes, Dad.

429
00:22:05,967 --> 00:22:07,367
You're leaving, Dad?

430
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:13,167
Sweetheart, the sooner
we can leave, the better.

431
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:16,500
It's better than getting
caught by your siblings.

432
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:18,067
Yeah, Coleen.

433
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,733
It'll be safer for all of us.

434
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:21,400
We won't have to be scared
anymore.

435
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,567
So, what happened?

436
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:38,567
Nothing.

437
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,933
He won't say where Manuel is.

438
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:43,200
Maybe he really doesn't know?

439
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,067
He knows.

440
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,767
I can feel it. I know he does.

441
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:51,767
Looks like he's just
protecting Felma.

442
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:52,733
Relax.

443
00:22:52,867 --> 00:22:54,400
You still have me.

444
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:56,933
Once I become a business
partner at FMP,

445
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:59,000
I'll find out
where your husband is.

446
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:00,067
No.

447
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:03,367
I don't have the
patience to wait.

448
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:06,867
Since we're already here
at Felma's office,

449
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,900
might as well go
straight to her.

450
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:10,033
Hazel, no.

451
00:23:10,167 --> 00:23:11,267
Wait here.

452
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,900
They can't see us together
or find out we know each other.

453
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:32,233
Thanks for the ride, Joel.

454
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:32,933
Oh, don't mention it.

455
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:34,633
Go on, go to your sister.

456
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:36,000
I'll wait here for you.

457
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:36,867
No, it's okay.

458
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,600
I've already bothered you
enough.

459
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:41,067
Andrea, I don't know the
whole story

460
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,133
behind what's going on,

461
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:45,067
but I hope things get better.

462
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,400
And one more thing, Andrea...

463
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:50,433
if you ever need someone
to talk to or want to open up,

464
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:51,900
just call me, okay?

465
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,667
You've got a new friend now.

466
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,600
Let's go to a coffee shop
sometime.

467
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:57,167
I'll listen. Okay?

468
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:58,600
- I'm your friend.
- Thanks again.

469
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:08,700
Are you on your way
to that meeting outside?

470
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:10,033
I canceled it.

471
00:24:10,167 --> 00:24:11,333
I couldn't focus.

472
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:13,900
I need to talk to Andrea.

473
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:15,233
She already left.

474
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:16,267
Where did she go?

475
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,600
I don't know.

476
00:24:18,733 --> 00:24:19,867
Oh, no.

477
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,400
<i> Let go of me!</i>

478
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:22,767
<i> I'll sue you!</i>

479
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,100
Hey!

480
00:24:24,233 --> 00:24:25,333
Let go of me!

481
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,333
- I'll sue you for harassment!
- What are you doing here?

482
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:28,933
What are you even doing here?

483
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:36,233
Just tell me where Manuel
and Jessica are hiding.

484
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:37,567
Please, have some mercy.

485
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:39,767
Oh, stop with the drama already,
Hazel.

486
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,633
For heaven's sake, just leave!

487
00:24:41,767 --> 00:24:43,600
Leave my friend alone!

488
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:46,067
I'm not being dramatic, Paz.

489
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,867
Did you forget?

490
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,900
Back when I came to you?

491
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:52,233
I was completely
at rock bottom.

492
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:54,733
I was desperate, Paz.

493
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:56,267
Do you remember that?

494
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,867
You said you'd help me.

495
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,033
- Hey!
- That's why you gave me

496
00:24:59,167 --> 00:25:00,200
Manuel's address.

497
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:00,900
But...

498
00:25:01,033 --> 00:25:02,567
but when I got there,

499
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:03,567
Manuel and Jessica
were already gone.

500
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:04,967
They escaped me!

501
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:08,667
That's why you gave me
Felma's address!

502
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,600
So that I could find them there,

503
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:12,233
because you believed
they were there.

504
00:25:12,367 --> 00:25:15,133
- You yourself believed!
- You lying, worthless rat!

505
00:25:15,267 --> 00:25:16,333
Didn't you believe it, too?

506
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:18,367
That Felma really is hiding
my husband and daughter?

507
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:20,067
So please...

508
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:21,000
Felma...

509
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:22,200
- Felma, I'm begging you.
- You liar!

510
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:24,100
You lying little rat!

511
00:25:24,233 --> 00:25:26,200
The only reason I gave you
Felma's address

512
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:27,633
is because you tricked me!

513
00:25:27,767 --> 00:25:29,200
Felma, I'm begging you.

514
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:31,767
- He's my husband!
- Get out! You liar!

515
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:32,667
Felma, please, I'm begging you.

516
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,533
Don't touch my friend! Get out!

517
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,933
-Give me back my husband, Felma!
-You liar!

518
00:25:38,067 --> 00:25:39,033
You're insane!

519
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:41,133
- Get out!
- Have mercy!

520
00:25:49,233 --> 00:25:50,833
You betrayed me.

521
00:25:50,967 --> 00:25:53,400
Felma, I'm begging you, please.

522
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:55,900
Hear me out first, okay?

523
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:56,633
Please.

524
00:25:56,767 --> 00:25:58,267
Rona, where's Coleen?

525
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,833
She didn't come to school today.

526
00:26:00,967 --> 00:26:02,367
But she called me earlier.

527
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:06,433
She said she'd spend
special time

528
00:26:06,567 --> 00:26:08,367
with some important people
for now.

529
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,900
Coleen?

530
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:11,333
Andrea?

531
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:12,567
What are you cooking?

532
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:16,367
Is that for your bonding time
with those very special

533
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:18,100
and important people?

534
00:26:18,233 --> 00:26:20,700
Jessica, Mrs. Wilson is calling.

535
00:26:20,833 --> 00:26:21,933
I remember it now.

536
00:26:22,067 --> 00:26:24,533
So, you are Jessica.

537
